<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,219,563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Male, wings fully developed, 
<quantity box="[709,791,219,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" unit="mm" value="1.9">1,9 mm</quantity>
. Reddish-brown, elytra with a rounded, not well-defined black spot in the medium part and a little black spot on the apex of each elytron (
<figureCitation box="[422,485,277,300]" captionStart="Figs 3-4" captionStartId="4.[178,218,945,967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1084,224,927]" captionTargetId="figure-92@4.[178,1084,212,935]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 3-4: (3) Micrambe yunnanensis nov.sp. from China (Yunnan), male; (4) Micrambe zhejiangensis nov.sp. from China (Zhejiang), male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5357070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5357070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Eyes conical. Pronotum 1,5 times broader than long, broadest between the anterior angles, strongly punctate, margin with strong teeth, surface very convex, sloping towards the margin, anterior callosities strongly prominent, margin nearly straight. Elytra stout, hairs uniform semi-erected, shoulders well developed, strongly punctate on the anterior part, less to the posterior part. Legs slender, tarsi with five segments, posterior tarsi with four segments (only in male), anterior tarsi segments 1-4 moderately widened (only in male). Antennae slender, club well developed, segments 3-7 longer than broad and equal, segment 8 shorter but not moniliform, segment 9 and 10 strong conical, segment 11 long as broad, rounded and conical. Parameres as in fig. 8.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[178,1086,579,747]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
C o m m e n t Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="JOHNSON et al." authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="PANZER" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[577,734,579,600]" class="Insecta" family="Cryptophagidae" genus="Micrambe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis box="[577,734,579,600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">M. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="GROUVELLE" authorityYear="1910" box="[802,925,579,600]" class="Insecta" family="Cryptophagidae" genus="Micrambe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[802,925,579,600]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">M. sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its strong punctuation (pronotum, elytra), Parameres strongly triangular (fig. 8). Very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Cryptophagidae" genus="Micrambe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">M. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished by the prominent callosity and the parameres. Also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(REITTER, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="REITTER" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[178,531,667,689]" class="Insecta" family="Cryptophagidae" genus="Micrambe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="micramboides">
<emphasis box="[178,355,667,688]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">M. micramboides</emphasis>
(REITTER, 1874)
</taxonomicName>
, which is strongly stout, with a pronotum broader and with rounded margins (fig. 11). Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Esser, 2017" authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="2017" box="[713,842,696,718]" class="Insecta" family="Cryptophagidae" genus="Micrambe" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuelkei" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis box="[713,842,696,718]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">M. schuelkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[850,924,696,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by its rounded, not well-defined spot.
</paragraph>
